data.text:
Jeffery Michael "Jeff" Gordon (born August 4, 1971) is an American stock car racing legend and part-time broadcaster of NASCAR telecasts for Fox NASCAR. He is especially known for driving in the NASCAR Cup Series for the Hendrick Motorsports team from 1990 to 2016 and is currently the team's vice chairman.

He voiced Jeff Gorvette (the car version of himself) in Cars 2 and Cars 2: The Video Game, and reprised his role in Cars 3.
